[CONTEXT LOG]
timestamp: 2026-05-07T19:42:00+07:00
current_task: Initialize project and plan prototype structure
summary: Set up React-TS frontend and planned simulation architecture for the blockchain prototype.
active_goals: Implement a minimalist, glassmorphic UI; build a JS-based mock blockchain logic for the UI to interact with.
recent_changes: Initialized frontend using create-vite.
decisions: Using a frontend-only mock blockchain first to rapidly prototype the UI and interaction logic per the design preferences, before connecting to a real Hardhat network if needed.
assumptions: The user's main goal is proving the concept via a visual prototype.
constraints: Use Vanilla CSS. Ensure UI matches "Minimalism, Glassmorphism, Liquid Glass".
risks: Building a full Hardhat setup might be overkill for a pure UI prototype, so a mock JS blockchain is safer for rapid visual iteration.
next_steps: Install dependencies, create UI components, and build JS mock blockchain classes.

